<Author>luisGranada_Spain
<Content>Awful!! We stayed at the Husa Arenas in June 2008. Staff and food were okay. The worst part was: they never informed us that the A/C was not working. I thought I did not know how to manage the A/C buttoms and was embarrassed to call reception... then, they let us know the A/C was broken up and unsure when it would go....indeed, it never worked out during the three-day stay and no alternative hotel or any compensation was provided. As a result, we had to sleep with opened windows and being awaken at 6am because of the sun and traffic noise (and by the way, very noise rooms). I agree...not a 4-star hotel..if it was in the past, not now. Quite far from the centre as well.Not recommended at all. 
