<Author>TravelGalore
<Content>If you are looking for a real 4-star, this is definitely not it! The hotel is clean, large storage areas, and bathrooms have been renovated. Staff is very friendly and the food in the restaurant is good. Location is also good and this where visitors to the neighboring university are suggested to stay. However, here is the problem: if this is a 4-star Hotel, then my house is Chateau Versailles! I organized a course and suggested to 20 people to stay there: I was embarrassed. It is the biggest lie anyone can make. This is a 2-star hotel, at most 3-stars (pushing it) old beat-up furniture, Austin Powers-style, dating from the time of Cervantes. No robes, no iron, no slippers, no coffee machine, incredibly small elevator (if you press on 8th floor before pressing on 4th floor it goes to 8 and then the other person has to come back to 4; only works in sequence!!!!), no sound insulation between rooms (you can hear your neighbor snore) and the bathroom amenities are up to the cleaning staff: they leave you some or nothing, depending on their mood. 
